{
  "texts": [
    "Accuracy show high values at either high or low prevalence and low values when prevalence is close to 0.5.",
    "However, it does have low values when the decision threshold is either close to 0 or 1 and the corresponding prevalence is low or high.",
    "As expected, AUC is invariant to decision threshold change as it always considers all possible thresholds already.",
    "And it is largely invariant to prevalence change as the range of its values is between 0.",
    "Variance of rankings of models by different metrics."
  ]
}